article.headline: Ark.-Little Rock 78, FIU 70
article.story: MIAMI -- Alex Garcia-Mendoza and Matt Mouzy scored 15 points each to lead Arkansas-Little Rock to a 78-70 victory over Florida International on Thursday night. Garcia-Mendoza scored consecutive field goals late in the second half and Mouzy's 3-pointer with 2:01 remaining gave the Trojans a 70-60 lead and secured their fourth straight win. Chuck Guy and Solomon Bozeman finished with 12 points each for the Trojans (12-9, 4-2 Sun Belt Conference). Florida International rallied from a 43-28 halftime deficit with a 15-4 run in the first 4:09 of the second half. Marvin Roberts and Phil Gary each had three-point plays and Allen's basket with 15:51 remaining capped the spurt and put the Panthers within 47-43. Arkansas-Little Rock responded with six unanswered points in the next 3:50. Allen led Florida International (8-10, 3-3) with a game-high 18 points.
